  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Describe the feature you would like\r\n\r\nFor example if I've configured `ftm-testnet` like so: \r\n```\r\n[rpc_endpoints]\r\nftm-testnet = \"${FTM_TESTNET_RPC}\"\r\n\r\n[etherscan]\r\n[etherscan.ftm-testnet]\r\nurl = \"https://testnet.ftmscan.com\"\r\nkey = \"${FTMSCAN_API_KEY}\"\r\n```\r\nWhen I attempt to run the script with `--verify` \r\n```\r\nforge script script/Counter.s.sol:CounterScript \\\r\n\t\t--rpc-url $FTM_TESTNET_RPC --broadcast --verify -vvvv\r\n```\r\n\r\nI want forge to read the API key for verification from the env var that I've specified in the `foundry.toml` file. This currently doesn't work unless I have a `ETHERSCAN_API_KEY` variable set. Looks like foundry's currently expecting an explicit `ETHERSCAN_API_KEY` variable set, which would be inconvenient when I'm deploying to multiple chains. \r\n\r\n### Additional context\r\n\r\n_No response_",
